ttps://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/140243407?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico","html_url":"https://github.com/mserico","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/mserico/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Background\n\nAfter extending the `Application` object with reverse proxy fields (see #XXXX), this issue implements the actual reverse proxy functionality. The core logic should be ported from [CasWAF](https://github.com/casbin/caswaf)'s `proxy/` and `service/` packages. The goal is to make Casdoor work like Nginx: receive HTTP requests on a public port, match the `Host` header to an Application's `Domain`, and forward the request to the configured upstream `ProxyHost:ProxyPort`.\n\n### Key code to reuse from CasWAF\n\n- **`service/proxy.go`** — contains the main reverse proxy handler using Go's `net/http/httputil.ReverseProxy`. Reference: https://github.com/casbin/caswaf/blob/master/service/proxy.go\n- **`proxy/`** — helper utilities for proxy handling\n- **Domain matching logic** — looks up the incoming request's `Host` header against all configured `Site.Domain` values to find the correct backend\n\n### What to implement\n\n1. **Port CasWAF's reverse proxy handler to Casdoor**\n   - Create a new package (e.g., `proxy/`) in Casdoor\n   - Implement a `http.Handler` that:\n     1. Reads the `Host` header from the incoming request\n     2. Looks up the matching `Application` by its `Domain` (or `OtherDomains`) field\n     3. If found, forwards the request to `ProxyHost:ProxyPort` using `httputil.ReverseProxy`\n     4. If not found, returns 404 or passes through to the normal Beego handler\n   - Port the relevant helper functions from CasWAF's `service/proxy.go`\n\n2. **Start a separate HTTP listener for the proxy**\n   - The proxy should listen on a configurable port (e.g., `80` for HTTP, 443 for HTTPS), separate from the Beego API port (default `8000`)\n   - Add configuration in `conf/app.conf`: `proxyPort = 80` (default empty = proxy disabled)\n   - When `proxyPort` is configured, Casdoor starts an additional HTTP listener on that port\n\n3. **Request header handling**\n   - Set standard reverse proxy headers: `X-Real-IP`, `X-Forwarded-For`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-Host`\n   - Support WebSocket upgrade (pass through `Upgrade` and `Connection` headers), as CasWAF does\n\n4. **Application lookup caching**\n   - Cache the `Domain → Application` mapping in memory for performance\n   - Refresh cache when an Application is created/updated/deleted\n\n### Non-goals (separate issues)\n\n- HTTPS / TLS termination (handled by the cert issue)\n- WAF rules / firewall (not needed in Casdoor)\n- OAuth proxy (Casdoor already has its own auth; this is not needed at the proxy layer for now)\n\n### Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] When an Application has `Domain=blog.example.com` and `ProxyHost=localhost:3000`, HTTP requests to `blog.example.com` on the proxy port are forwarded to `localhost:3000`\n- [ ] Proxy headers (`X-Forwarded-For`, etc.) are correctly set\n- [ ] Applications without `Domain` configured are not affected\n- [ ] The Beego API port continues to work independently\n\n### References\n\n- CasWAF proxy handler: https://github.com/casbin/caswaf/blob/master/service/proxy.go\n- CasWAF overview (reverse proxy): https://caswaf.org/docs/overview/\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/casdoor/casdoor/issues/5111/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/casdoor/casdoor/issues/5111/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ldez/golangci-lint-bench/issues/63","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ldez/golangci-lint-bench","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ldez/golangci-lint-bench/issues/63/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ldez/golangci-lint-bench/issues/63/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ldez/golangci-lint-bench/issues/63/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ldez/golangci-lint-bench/issues/63","id":4288036354,"node_id":"I_kwDOMLDMIM7_lj4C","number":63,"title":"benchmark: PR 6485 (clickhouselint)","user":{"login":"ldez","id":5674651,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU2NzQ2NTE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5674651?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez","html_url":"https://github.com/ldez","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ldez/received_events","type":