ts_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[{"login":"BasilSuhail","id":233993185,"node_id":"U_kgDODfJz4Q","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/233993185?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail","html_url":"https://github.com/BasilSuhail","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-04-03T21:52:06Z","updated_at":"2026-04-03T22:49:10Z","closed_at":"2026-04-03T22:49:10Z","assignee":{"login":"BasilSuhail","id":233993185,"node_id":"U_kgDODfJz4Q","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/233993185?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail","html_url":"https://github.com/BasilSuhail","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/BasilSuhail/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"MEMBER","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\nAdd **openvpn-ui** (https://github.com/d3vilh/openvpn-ui) as a self-hosted VPN manager to HomeForge. Starts automatically with `./boom.sh`, accessible via a dashboard tile on port 8087. Cert management, client profile generation, and QR codes all available through a browser UI — no CLI required.\n\n**Full design log:** `Project_S_Logs/20_OpenVPN_UI_Integration.md` on branch `feat/openvpn-ui-integration`\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nBrowser → http://<host>:8087 → project-s-openvpn-ui (GoLang/Beego)\n                                          │\n                          ┌───────────────┴───────────────┐\n                          │  shared volumes ./data/vpn/   │\n                          │  /var/run/docker.sock (r/o)   │\n                          └───────────────┬───────────────┘\n                                          │\n                               project-s-openvpn\n                               (OpenVPN daemon, 1194/UDP)\n```\n\nTwo containers. The UI container manages PKI and config files on shared volumes and uses the Docker socket (read-only) to restart the OpenVPN container when certs change.\n\n---\n\n## Port Allocation\n\n| Port | Protocol | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| **8087** | TCP | OpenVPN UI web interface (no conflict with existing stack) |\n| **1194** | UDP | OpenVPN tunnel traffic |\n| 2080 | TCP | Management socket — internal only, not host-exposed |\n\n---\n\n## Docker Compose Changes\n\n```yaml\n  openvpn:\n    image: d3vilh/openvpn-server:latest\n    container_name: project-s-openvpn\n    privileged: true\n    cap_add:\n      - NET_ADMIN\n    ports:\n      - \"1194:1194/udp\"\n    volumes:\n      - ./data/vpn:/etc/openvpn\n    restart: unless-stopped\n\n  openvpn-ui:\n    image: d3vilh/openvpn-ui:latest\n    container_name: project-s-openvpn-ui\n    privileged: true\n    depends_on:\n      - openvpn\n    ports:\n      - \"8087:8080\"\n    environment:\n      - OPENVPN_ADMIN_USERNAME=${VPN_ADMIN_USERNAME:-admin}\n      - OPENVPN_ADMIN_PASSWORD=${VPN_ADMIN_PASSWORD}\n    volumes:\n      - ./data/vpn:/etc/openvpn\n      - ./data/vpn/db:/opt/openvpn-ui/db\n      - ./data/vpn/pki:/usr/share/easy-rsa/pki\n      - /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock:ro\n    restart: unless-stopped\n```\n\n---\n\n## Volume Layout\n\nAll VPN state under `./data/vpn/` (consistent with HomeForge pattern):\n\n```\n./data/vpn/\n├── pki/              # CA, server cert, client certs, CRL, DH params, TA key  ⚠️ back this up\n├── clients/          # Generated .ovpn profile files\n├── config/\n│   ├── client.conf   # Client profile template\n│   └── easy-rsa.vars # PKI settings\n├── staticclients/    # CCD files for static IP assignments\n├── log/              # OpenVPN logs\n├── db/               # openvpn-ui SQLite DB (UI users, settings)\n├── server.conf       # OpenVPN server config\n└── fw-rules.sh       # Firewall hook\n```\n\n---\n\n## Seed Config Files\n\nSeed templates ship in `config/vpn/` in the repo. `boom.sh` / `install.sh` copy them to `./data/vpn/` on first run only (conditional on `server.conf` not already existing — safe to re-run without overwriting a live PKI):\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p ./data/vpn/{pki,clients,config,staticclients,log,db}\nif [ ! -f ./data/vpn/server.conf ]; then\n  cp -r ./config/vpn/. ./data/vpn/\nfi\n```\n\n---\n\n## .env.example additions\n\n```env\n# OpenVPN UI\nVPN_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin\nVPN_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change_me_vpn_password\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dashboard Tile\n\nIn `welcome-section.tsx`, add to `SERVICE_PORTS`:\n\n```typescript\n{ name: \"VPN Manager\", port: 8087, icon: Shield },\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `docker-compose.yml` — add `openvpn` and `openvpn-ui` services\n- [ ] `boom.sh` — `mkdir -p ./data/vpn/{...}` + conditional seed config copy\n- [ ] `install.sh` — same as boom.sh\n- [ ] `.env.example` — add `VPN_ADMIN_USERNAME`, `VPN_ADMIN_PASSWORD`\n- [ ] `config/vpn/server.conf` — seed server config template\n- [ ] `config/vpn/client.conf` — seed client config template\n- [ ] `config/vpn/easy-rsa.vars` — seed EasyRSA vars template\n- [ ] `config/vpn/fw-rules.sh` — empty firewall hook script\n- [ ] `Dashboard/Dashboard1/components/dashboard/welcome-section.tsx` — add VPN tile\n\n---\n\n## Known Limitations (non-blocking for MVP)\n\n| Limitation | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| No built-in HTTPS | Plain HTTP on 8087 — LAN-only for MVP, TLS via reverse proxy later |\n| No subpath support | Must use port or subdomain, cannot be served at `/vpn` |\n| Privileged containers | Required for iptables/OpenVPN — accepted trade-off |\n| Docker socket access | Read-only mount `:ro` mitigates blast radius |\n| External access needs port-forward | Forward 1194 UDP on router for remote VPN access |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- Full design log: `Project_S_Logs/20_OpenVPN_UI_Integration.md`\n- Branch: `feat/openvpn-ui-integration`\n- openvpn-ui: https://github.com/d3vilh/openvpn-ui\n- openvpn-server: https://github.com/d3vilh/openvpn-server\n- Proposed by: Saad Shafique","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dlobs-co/dhobs/issues/77/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dlobs-co/dhobs/issues/77/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"http