hub.com/users/hsluoyz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/hsluoyz/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},{"login":"Copilot","id":198982749,"node_id":"BOT_kgDOC9w8XQ","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/1143301?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot","html_url":"https://github.com/apps/copilot-swe-agent","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/received_events","type":"Bot","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-02-15T08:36:17Z","updated_at":"2026-02-15T09:00:25Z","closed_at":"2026-02-15T09:00:25Z","assignee":{"login":"Copilot","id":198982749,"node_id":"BOT_kgDOC9w8XQ","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/in/1143301?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot","html_url":"https://github.com/apps/copilot-swe-agent","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Copilot/received_events","type":"Bot","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"MEMBER","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Summary\n\nCasdoor currently serves authorization server metadata only at the OpenID Connect discovery endpoint `/.well-known/openid-configuration`. It does **not** serve metadata at `/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server` as defined by [RFC 8414](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8414). This endpoint is critical for MCP (Model Context Protocol) authorization, where MCP clients are required to attempt discovery from `/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server` **first**, before falling back to `/.well-known/openid-configuration`.\n\n### Background\n\nRFC 8414 defines `/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server` as the standard endpoint for **general-purpose OAuth 2.0** authorization server metadata. `/.well-known/openid-configuration` was originally defined by OpenID Connect Discovery 1.0 for OIDC-specific scenarios. While the two endpoints serve nearly identical JSON payloads, they exist as separate standards:\n\n- `/.well-known/openid-configuration` → defined by OpenID Connect Discovery 1.0\n- `/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server` → defined by RFC 8414 for general OAuth 2.0\n\nRFC 8414 Section 5 explicitly acknowledges the overlap and notes that both can coexist. Many IAM products (e.g., Keycloak, PingFederate, Auth0) serve both.\n\nThe [MCP Authorization specification](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/2025-06-18/basic/authorization) defines the following discovery priority order for MCP clients:\n\nFor root issuer URLs (e.g., `https://auth.example.com`):\n1. `https://auth.example.com/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server` **(try first)**\n2. `https://auth.example.com/.well-known/openid-configuration` **(fallback)**\n\nFor issuer URLs with path components (e.g., `https://auth.example.com/tenant1`):\n1. `https://auth.example.com/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server/tenant1`\n2. `https://auth.example.com/.well-known/openid-configuration/tenant1`\n\nWithout `/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server`, every MCP client connecting to Casdoor will:\n1. Hit a **404** on the first discovery attempt\n2. Fall back to `/.well-known/openid-configuration` and succeed\n\nThis is functionally correct but has several downsides:\n- Adds unnecessary latency (one extra round-trip per client connection)\n- Generates noisy 404 error logs on the Casdoor side\n- May break **strict** MCP clients that do not implement the fallback (the MCP Inspector project already had a [related compatibility bug](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/inspector/issues/563))\n\n### Current State in Casdoor\n\nCasdoor registers only the OIDC discovery routes in its router:\n\n```go\n// routers/router.go (current)\nbeego.Router(\"/.well-known/openid-configuration\", &controllers.RootController{}, \"GET:GetOidcDiscovery\")\nbeego.Router(\"/.well-known/:applicationName/openid-configuration\", &controllers.RootController{}, \"GET:GetOidcDiscovery\")\n```\n\nThe handler calls `object.GetOidcDiscovery(host)` which returns an `OidcDiscovery` struct. There is **no route** for `/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server`.\n\nThe current `/.well-known/openid-configuration` response includes:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"issuer\": \"https://door.casdoor.com\",\n  \"authorization_endpoint\": \"https://door.casdoor.com/login/oauth/authorize\",\n  \"token_endpoint\": \"https://door.casdoor.com/api/login/oauth/access_token\",\n  \"userinfo_endpoint\": \"https://door.casdoor.com/api/userinfo\",\n  \"jwks_uri\": \"https://door.casdoor.com/.well-known/jwks\",\n  \"introspection_endpoint\": \"https://door.casdoor.com/api/login/oauth/introspect\",\n  \"response_types_supported\": [\"code\", \"token\", \"id_token\", ...],\n  \"grant_types_supported\": [\"authorization_code\", \"implicit\", \"password\", ...],\n  \"scopes_supported\": [\"openid\", \"email\", \"profile\", \"address\", \"phone\", \"offline_access\"],\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nNote that it is also **missing** `code_challenge_methods_supported`, even though Casdoor already supports PKCE with S256. This field is important for MCP clients to confirm PKCE support before initiating the auth flow.\n\n### Proposed Implementation\n\n**1. Add new routes in `routers/router.go`:**\n\n```go\n// OAuth 2.0 Authorization Server Metadata (RFC 8414)\nbeego.Router(\"/.well-known/oauth-authorization-server\", &controllers.RootController{}, \"GET:GetOAuthServerMetadata\")\nbeego.Router(\"/.well-known/:applicationName/oauth-authorization-server\", &controllers.RootController{}, \"GET:GetOAuthServerMetadata\")\n```\n\n**2. Implement the controller method:**\n\nThe simplest and most maintainable approach is to **reuse `GetOidcDiscovery()`** internally, since the response format is nearly identical:\n\n```go\nfunc (c *RootController) GetOAuthServerMetadata() {\n    host := c.Ctx.Request.Host\n    applicationName := c.GetString(\":applicationName\")\n    \n    // Reuse the existing OIDC discovery data\n    discovery := object.GetOidcDiscovery(host, applicationName)\n    \n    // Build the RFC 8414 response (same fields, with OAuth 2.0 additions)\n    metadata := object.BuildOAuthServerMetadata(discovery, host)\n    \n    c.Data[\"json\"] = metadata\n    c.ServeJSON()\n}\n```\n\n**3. Add missing fields to both endpoints:**\n\nCreate a shared helper that augments the base OIDC discovery data with fields required by RFC 8414 and the MCP spec:\n\n```go\nfunc BuildOAuthServerMetadata(oidc OidcDiscovery, host string) map[string]interface{} {\n    metadata := map[string]interface{}{\n        // All existing OIDC discovery fields\n        \"issuer\":                   oidc.Issuer,\n        \"authorization_endpoint\":   oidc.AuthorizationEndpoint,\n        \"token_endpoint\":           oidc.TokenEndpoint,\n        \"userinfo_endpoint\":        oidc.UserinfoEndpoint,\n        \"jwks_uri\":                 oidc.JwksUri,\n        \"introspection_endpoint\":   oidc.IntrospectionEndpoint,\n        \"response_types_supported\": oidc.ResponseTypesSupported,\n        \"grant_types_supported\":    oidc.GrantTypesSupported,\n        \"scopes_supported\":         oidc.ScopesSupported,\n        \"subject_types_supported\":  oidc.SubjectTypesSupported,\n        \n        // Fields currently missing but needed for MCP compatibility\n        \"code_challenge_methods_supported\": []string{\"S256\"},\n        \"token_endpoint_auth_methods_supported\": []string{\n            \"client_secret_basic\",\n            \"client_secret_post\",\n            \"none\", // for public clients using PKCE\n        },\n        \n        // Will be added after DCR is implemented:\n        // \"registration_endpoint\": host + \"/api/oauth/register\",\n    }\n    return metadata\n}\n```\n\n**4. Also update `/.well-known/openid-configuration`:**\n\nThe existing `OidcDiscovery` struct should be updated to include `code_challenge_methods_supported`:\n\n```go\ntype OidcDiscovery struct {\n    // ... existing fields ...\n    CodeChallengeMethodsSupported []string `json:\"code_challenge_methods_supported\"`\n}\n```\n\nAnd set it in `GetOidcDiscovery()`:\n\n```go\nfunc GetOidcDiscovery(host string) OidcDiscovery {\n    return OidcDiscovery{\n        // ... existing fields ...\n        CodeChallengeMethodsSupported: []string{\"S256\"},\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis ensures both endpoints advertise PKCE support, which Casdoor already has.\n\n### Implementation Cost\n\nThis is a **low-effort, high-value** change:\n- Add 2 new routes pointing to a new handler\n- The new handler reuses `GetOidcDiscovery()` and adds a few extra fields\n- Add `code_challenge_methods_supported` to the existing `OidcDiscovery` struct\n- No database changes, no new dependencies\n\n### References\n\n- RFC 8414: https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8414\n- RFC 8414 Section 5 (compatibility with OIDC Discovery): https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8414#section-5\n- MCP Authorization spec (discovery priority): https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/2025-06-18/basic/authorization\n- MCP Inspector compatibility issue: https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/inspector/issues/563\n- Related: #4750 (MCP server for Casdoor)","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/casdoor/casdoor/issues/5093/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/casdoor/casdoor/issues/5093/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/udistrital/sga_documentacion_inversion/issues/5","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/udistrital/sga_documentacion_inversion","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/udistrital/sga_documentacion_inversion/issues/5/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/udistrital/sga_documentacion_inversion/issues/5/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/udistrital/sga_documentacion_inversion/issues/5/events","html_url":"https://github.com/udistrital/sga_documentacion_inversion/issues/5","id":3845186145,"node_id":"I_kwDOQ-YeRs7lMOJh","number":5,"title":"Capacitación inicial","user":{"login":"diagutierrezro","id":38676533,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM4Njc2NTMz","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38676533?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/diagutierrezro","html_url":"https://github.com/diagutierrezro","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/diagutierrezro/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/diagutierrezro/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.githu