e":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/milestones/16","html_url":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/milestone/16","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gofiber/fiber/milestones/16/labels","id":15684155,"node_id":"MI_kwDODfYWS84A71I7","number":16,"title":"v3.2.0","description":"https://github.com/gofiber/fiber/releases/tag/v3.2.0","creator":{"login":"ReneWerner87","id":7063188,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjcwNjMxODg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7063188?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87","html_url":"https://github.com/ReneWerner87","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ReneWerner87/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":93,"state":"closed","created_at":"2026-04-25T10:53:13Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T10:59:04Z","due_on":"2026-04-25T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T10:58:51Z"},"comments":13,"created_at":"2026-02-27T16:42:22Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T10:54:37Z","closed_at":"2026-03-04T07:33:00Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Bug Description\n\nI've stumbled upon two bugs when it comes to query parameters binding, when the parameter appears multiple times:\n1. `\"/test?field[]=a&field[]=b\")` - bound with `query:\"field[]\"` - will lead to `nil`  for the `field` value.\n2. `\"/test?single[]=a\"` - bound with `query:\"single\"` - will lead to `\"a\"` for the `single` field, causing potential data corruption.\n\nI could also try to fix those issues, but I'm not sure about the reasoing. In my opinion, the binding should be as \"stupid\" as possible, only regarding the exact name, and collect multiple occurences of it. But I guess there was more to it, like how it's supposed to handle data from other sources than the query params.\n\n### How to Reproduce\n\nRun the test below and see them fail.\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\n1. Binding for `\"/test?field[]=a&field[]=b\")` should return `[a, b]` (e.g, in form of a `string` slice).\n2. Binding for `\"/test?single[]=a\"` should return `\"\"` when the tag's description doesn't exactly match the name.\n\n### Fiber Version\n\nv3.1.0\n\n### Code Snippet (optional)\n\n```go\npackage main\n\nimport (\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"net/http/httptest\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\t\"github.com/gofiber/fiber/v3\"\n\t\"github.com/stretchr/testify/assert\"\n)\n\ntype sliceParams struct {\n\tFields []string `query:\"field[]\"`\n}\n\ntype singleParams struct {\n\tSingleField string `query:\"single\"`\n}\n\nfunc newApp[T any](t *testing.T, out *T) *fiber.App {\n\tt.Helper()\n\tapp := fiber.New()\n\tapp.Get(\"/test\", func(c fiber.Ctx) error {\n\t\treturn c.Bind().Query(out)\n\t})\n\treturn app\n}\n\nfunc get(t *testing.T, app *fiber.App, url string) {\n\tt.Helper()\n\treq := httptest.NewRequest(http.MethodGet, url, nil)\n\tresp, err := app.Test(req)\n\tassert.NoError(t, err)\n\tassert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, resp.StatusCode)\n}\n\n// Bug 1: Bind().Query() does not bind bracket-style slice keys.\n// query:\"field[]\" should populate Fields from field[]=a&field[]=b, but yields nil.\n